<Layout 
  title="Legislation | Policy"
  description="Understand the key legislation governing the UK Armed Forces Compensation Scheme. Learn about the legal framework and recent legislative changes.">
  <div class="container my-5">
    <h1 class="display-4 mb-4">AFCS Legislation</h1>
    <div class="row g-4">
      <div class="col-lg-8">
        <p class="lead">The Armed Forces Compensation Scheme (AFCS) is underpinned by a robust legal framework. This page outlines the key legislation that governs the scheme and recent legislative changes that may affect your claim.</p>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Primary Legislation</h2>
        <p>The AFCS is primarily established under the following acts:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>The Armed Forces (Pensions and Compensation) Act 2004</li>
          <li>The Armed Forces and Reserve Forces (Compensation Scheme) Order 2011</li>
        </ul>
        <p>These acts set out the fundamental principles and structure of the scheme.</p>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Key Provisions</h2>
        <p>The legislation covers several crucial areas:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Eligibility criteria for compensation</li>
          <li>Types of injuries and illnesses covered</li>
          <li>Calculation methods for lump sum payments and ongoing pensions</li>
          <li>Time limits for claims</li>
          <li>Appeal processes</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Recent Legislative Changes</h2>
        <p>The AFCS is periodically reviewed and updated. Recent changes include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>The Armed Forces (Compensation Scheme) (Amendment) Order 2020</li>
          <li>Updates to the tariff of injuries in 2021</li>
          <li>Revisions to the claims process in 2022</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Interaction with Other Legislation</h2>
        <p>The AFCS legislation interacts with other relevant laws:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>The Armed Forces Covenant</li>
          <li>The Equality Act 2010</li>
          <li>Various international treaties and agreements</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Future Legislative Developments</h2>
        <p>The government regularly reviews the AFCS to ensure it meets the needs of service personnel. Potential future changes may include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Expansion of mental health provisions</li>
          <li>Updates to reflect new medical understanding of service-related conditions</li>
          <li>Adjustments to compensation levels in line with economic factors</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-4">
        <div class="card bg-light mb-4">
          <div class="card-body">
